5|$|Politically, Robinson opposed both secession and <b>abolition.</b> Though he had Union sympathies, he was {{considered}} a moderate, opposing both fugitive slave laws and the enlistment of black soldiers. As a state senator, he supported the Crittenden Compromise and opposed the Civil War. As governor, he drew criticism from the administration of President Abraham Lincoln for opposing the Emancipation Proclamation.|$|E
