5|$|Tameside {{was created}} on 1 April 1974, by the Local Government Act 1972 {{as one of}} the ten {{metropolitan}} districts of Greater Manchester. It took over the local government functions of nine districts which were formerly in the administrative counties of Lancashire and of Cheshire. In 1986 Tameside effectively became a unitary authority with the <b>abolition</b> of the Greater Manchester County Council.|$|E
